These instructions will guide an agent to
  install the Elasticsearch onboarding agent into a user's environment.

First fetch the content of the following files to analyze them for accuracy:
- Append snippet: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wildemat/kibana/search-agent/src/platform/packages/shared/kbn-search-agent/AGENT-elasticsearch-append.md
- Agents files directory: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wildemat/kibana/search-agent/src/platform/packages/shared/kbn-search-agent/.elasticsearch-agent


1. Verify the contents of the new directory are correct by comparing them to the Agents file.
2. If the contents are correct, proceed to the next step.
3. If the contents are not correct, ask the user to review the contents and correct them.
4. Append content from the Append snippet to the bottom of the current workspace's AGENTS.md file. Create one if it doesn't exist.
5. copy the contents of the .elasticsearch-agent directory into a new directory of the same name in the user's current workspace
6. Once the contents are correct, proceed to the next step.





